Windows: Ensure that LOG_FATAL errors are reported by Breakpad

Change NaClAbort() so that it will invoke Breakpad by crashing with a
HLT instruction instead of calling _exit().

Extend the existing Windows test case to cover LOG_FATAL and CHECK()
in addition to the memory access errors it covered before.

Move the test syscall out of test_host.c into service_runtime.  This
is in preparation for testing these crash cases in Chromium via
inbrowser_crash_test.

BUG=http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2626
TEST=run_windows_*_in_syscall_test

